<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="705" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d705">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War
                                    1939/2392</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary
                                        of State</hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-15">March 15,
                                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>The Ambassador<note n="35" xml:id="d705fn35">The French
                                        Ambassador, Gaston Henry-Haye.</note> called at his request.
                                    He said that health conditions in Syria were very bad and that
                                    his Government desired that this Government request the
                                    cooperation of Great Britain to permit medical products from the
                                    United States to be sent to Syria and Lebanon. I replied that I
                                    would be glad to take this matter up with the British.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ull</hi>]</signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>